    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-06-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-06-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="320" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d320">
                <head>No. 320.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Nelson</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                        the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-06-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 6, 1872</date>.
                                (Received June 28.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 581.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose herewith a
                            copy and translation (A and B) of a prolongation of the Tehuantepec
                            Railway and Canal concession, extending its time for three years longer,
                            which was granted to the Tehuantepec company by the Mexican congress on
                            the 22d of May last.</p>
                <p>* * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>THOMAS H. NELSON.</signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure B—Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <p>The Citizen President of the republic has been pleased to address me
                                the following decree:</p>
                    <p>Benito Juarez, constitutional President of the United States of
                                Mexico, to the inhabitants thereof: Know ye—</p>
                    <p>That the Congress of the Union has decreed as follows:</p>
                    <p>The concessions granted oh the 2d of January, 1869, and the 14th of
                                December, 1870, the former for the construction and management of a
                                railroad, and the latter for the construction of a canal, navigable
                                from ocean to ocean, across the Isthmus of Tehuantepec, are hereby
                                renewed.</p>
                    <pb facs="0527" n="431" xml:id="pg_431"/>
                    <p>The periods of time mentioned in the former shall he counted from the
                                2d of January of the present year.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <dateline rendition="#left">
                            <placeName>
                                <placeName type="venue">Hall
                                            of Sessions of the Congress of the Union</placeName>,
                                            <placeName type="city">Mexico</placeName>
                            </placeName>,
                                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-05-22">May 22,
                                        1872</date>.</dateline>
                        <lb/>
                        <signed>JOSÉ H. NUNEZ,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Deputy
                                    President</hi>.</signed>
                        <lb/>
                        <signed>JOSÉ FERNANDEZ,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Deputy
                                    Secretary</hi>.</signed>
                        <lb/>
                        <signed>ENRIQUE MARIA RUBIO,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Deputy
                                        Secretary.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                    <postscript>
                        <p>Therefore, I order the above to be printed, published,
                                    circulated, and duly obeyed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <dateline rendition="#left">
                                <placeName>
                                    <placeName type="venue">Palace of the Federal
                                                Government</placeName> of <placeName type="city">Mexico</placeName>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-05-22">May 22, 1872</date>.</dateline>
                            <lb/>
                            <signed>BENITO JUAREZ.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </postscript>
                    <postscript>
                        <p>The Citizen <hi rend="smallcaps">Blas Balcárcel</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister of Public Works, Colonization,
                                        Industry, and Commerce.</hi>
                        </p>
                    </postscript>
                    <postscript>
                        <p>And I communicate it to you for your information and consequent
                                    action.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <dateline rendition="#left">
                                <placeName>Mexico</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-05-22">May 22,
                                            1872</date>.</dateline>
                            <lb/>
                            <signed>BALCÁRCEL.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </postscript>
                </frus:attachment>
